<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc3ece42c-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7108"><num value="7108">§ 7108.</num><heading> Rejection of applications</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">An application for review on appeal shall not be entertained unless it is in conformity with this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc3ece42d-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(<ref href="/us/pl/85/857">Pub. L. 85–857</ref>, <date date="1958-09-02">Sept. 2, 1958</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/72/1243">72 Stat. 1243</ref>, § 4008; renumbered § 7108, <ref href="/us/pl/102/40/tIV/s402/b/1">Pub. L. 102–40, title IV, § 402(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="1991-05-07">May 7, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/238">105 Stat. 238</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
